text: Welcome to your suburban oasis in Round Rock's Paloma Lake community. The Craftsman-style door welcomes guests into the elegant foyer with coffered ceiling and stunning formal dining with sumptuous wood floors, also found in the living room & office. The gourmet kitchen will take your breath away with Euro-style hood, cabinets & counters galore, breakfast bar, & beautiful stainless steel built-in Kitchen Aid appliances. Nearby, the butler's pantry features a wine fridge, sink, & handy storage. The breakfast nook with window seat and wood shutters makes for a cozy start to the day and ensures everyone stays part of the action. A graceful archway leads to the living room overlooking the private backyard and into the office, perfect for a sunroom, playroom, or craft room. Moving into the primary suite, you'll feel transported a world away thanks to the bay window overlooking the landscaped yard, offering space for a sitting area, and the bath with dual vanities, an oversized shower with a bench, and an extra large closet. Two additional bedrooms featuring custom woodwork, a bath, a laundry room, and more storage round out the home. The gem of the home is the backyard with a large covered patio with a Kitchen Aid grill, a pergola-covered deck, a landscaped yard, and a rock wall fence. Additional home features include a 4' garage extension, a new 2-stage HVAC with a purifier in 2020, back windows in 2019-2020, and a new water softener in 2021. The home is a 90-second drive to lakeside amenities: fishing pond, sand volleyball, pickleball court, two parks/playgrounds, splash pad, bi-level pool, community center, and nearly five miles of trails around the lake & creek, plus additional parks and playgrounds. Less than a 10-minute drive to Toll Road 130 with further easy access to Toll Road 45 and I-35, and less than 15 minutes from shopping and dining in the University Oaks and Hutto areas, you'll never be at a loss for things to do!
